Rating: 4
This was not only fun to make but it was absolutely delicious. Had a bit of trouble when turning the chicken...it stuck to the roasting pan. Nevertheles the inside was wonderfully tender and the outside was perfectly crispy. I definitely recommend pairing it with the deglazing sauce.

Rating: 3
This was tasty, moist and crispy.

Rating: 4
I really enjoyed this recipe. I made the stuffing in the morning. I didn't cook on all 3 sides. I put in breast side up and cooked it fully from there. I served with sauteed potatoes and skillet-glazed baby carrots and sugar snap peas. I did find however that the chicken tended to smoke a lot when cooking. I had to open the windows to vent.

Rating: 3
This is a great recipe. I did not like to roast the chicken on the sides and move around.I put mine on a wire grill in a roasting pan breastside up at 350 basting once in a while. Turned out perfect, skin crisp, meat full of flavor from the stuffing. Serve with patato dumplings and haricots verts a la lyonnaise.